2. A communication apparatus comprising:
an encoder;
a modulator which generates a plurality of symbols on the basis of information inputted from the encoder;
a serial-parallel converter which generates a plurality of signals based on the symbols; and
an operation unit which generates a matrix randomly,
wherein the operation unit performs beam forming of the plurality of signals based on the matrix, and outputs beam formed signals corresponding to a plurality of antennas for outputting to a wireless network.

3. An information processing device comprising:
a modulation unit which generates a plurality of modulation symbols;
a conversion unit which converts the modulation symbol into M units of signals (2≦M);
an operation unit which performs beam forming of the M units of signals by using a complex matrix consisting of M×L units of elements, and outputs L units of beam formed signals (2≦L).
